+# v0.15 Config Init
+
+Date: 2026-06-09
+Phase: local config/init preview
+Status: PASS for local config creation and config-driven defaults
+
+## Goal
+
+Let users initialize Pala Memory Core once, then reuse local defaults for knowledge-bank backup, Drive-folder backup, mobile share folders, and dashboard host/port.
+
+## Added Behavior
+
+| Area | Change |
+|---|---|
+| CLI | Added `python pala.py init` |
+| Config | Writes ignored `pala.config.json` |
+| Example | Added committed `pala.config.example.json` |
+| Path precedence | CLI argument > environment variable > config > built-in default |
+| Doctor | Reports config file and config version |
+| Backup | `backup github` and `backup drive` read config defaults |
+| Report | `report vault` reads config paths for latest backup artifacts |
+| Dashboard | `dashboard serve` reads config host/port defaults |
+
+## Commands
+
+```powershell
+python .\pala.py init --force --knowledge-bank <repo> --drive-target <folder> --mobile-share <folder> --dashboard-port 8799 --create-targets
+python .\pala.py doctor --strict
+python .\pala.py backup github --all --push
+python .\pala.py backup drive --all
+python .\pala.py dashboard serve
+```
+
+## Smoke Test
+
+Executed in `C:\Users\Pala-Home-1\Desktop\Codex\pala-memory-core`:
+
+```powershell
+python -m py_compile .\pala.py
+python .\pala.py init --force --knowledge-bank .\data\backups\config-kb --drive-target .\data\backups\config-drive --mobile-share .\data\inbox\config-mobile --dashboard-port 8799 --create-targets
+git status --short --ignored pala.config.json pala.config.example.json .gitignore
+python .\pala.py backup drive --all
+python .\pala.py backup github --all --push
+python .\pala.py report vault --all --json
+python .\pala.py doctor --strict
+python .\pala.py dashboard serve
+```
+
+Observed key output:
+
+```text
+config saved pala.config.json
+knowledge_bank_path=...\data\backups\config-kb-git-...
+drive_backup_path=...\data\backups\config-drive-...
+mobile_share_path=...\data\inbox\config-mobile-...
+!! pala.config.json
+?? pala.config.example.json
+backup_status.github=complete updated=8
+PASS | config           | Config file | pala.config.json
+PASS | config           | Config version | version=1
+PASS | knowledge-bank   | Knowledge-bank repo | ...\config-kb-git-...
+PASS | drive            | Drive folder target | ...\config-drive-...
+status=200 stopped=<pid>
+```
+
+Dashboard verification:
+
+```text
+dashboard serve used configured port 8799
+GET http://127.0.0.1:8799 returned 200
+```
+
+## Release Posture
+
+This is a local setup preview. The config file is intentionally ignored by Git because it stores user-specific local paths. It does not install dependencies or create remote cloud resources automatically.
